nsuring I include action for advisory preparation regarding dependencies while avoiding restating deterministic guidelines.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Jackrabbit WebDAV is an in-process WebDAV client/server utility library, but its servlet-facing APIs depend on javax.servlet as a provided dependency, so meaningful coverage of request/response, IO, and servlet classes needs servlet API on the test classpath.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The resolved jackrabbit-webdav artifact declares javax.servlet:servlet-api as a provided dependency and exposes servlet-based APIs such as AbstractWebdavServlet, WebdavRequestImpl, WebdavResponseImpl, InputContextImpl, and OutputContextImpl. The existing 1.5.0 scaffold also adds servlet-api explicitly for these tests.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker service, external WebDAV server, environment variable, or system property appears necessary. Tests should exercise the library in-process using generated XML, WebDAV method/property objects, and simple servlet request/response fakes where needed.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact POM inherits servlet-api 2.3, while the existing scaffold uses 2.4; 2.4 is compatible for test fakes but local Gradle verification remains authoritative.\",\n    \"The reported native-image run failure may still require reachability metadata or test adjustments unrelated to setup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_076ab6a98355a1b4016a42980c9ee48197b686d55b8527e129\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1162, "output": 832, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33226, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "s